{"id":1115,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":1115,"title":"Shiloh","subtitle":"","short_title":"Shiloh","uri":"/scriptures/bd/shiloh","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/shiloh.t1","order":".000.3658"},[".title","Shiloh"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/shiloh.p1","order":".000.3659"},"(1) A sacred city of the Holy Land, 9¼ miles north from Bethel and 11½ miles south from Shechem, in the tribe of Ephraim (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/18.1"},"Josh. 18:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/18.31"},"Judg. 18:31"],"). The tabernacle was here during the greater part of the period of the Judges, and the place continued to be the religious center of the nation (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/1.3"},"1 Sam. 1:3"],") until after the loss of the Ark in the disastrous battle of Ebenezer. See also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/22.9,12"},"Josh. 22:9, 12"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/21.12-23"},"Judg. 21:12–23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/1.24"},"1 Sam. 1:24"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/3.21"},"3:21"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/4.3-4"},"4:3–4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/14.3"},"14:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/2.27"},"1 Kgs. 2:27"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/14.2,4"},"14:2, 4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/78.60"},"Ps. 78:60"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/7.12-14"},"Jer. 7:12–14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/26.6"},"26:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/41.5"},"41:5"],"."],["div",{"id":"p2","uri":"/scriptures/bd/shiloh.p2","order":".000.3660"},"(2) The name as found in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/49.10"},"Gen. 49:10"],"has been regarded by many biblical scholars as a prophecy of the coming of Messiah. This interpretation is confirmed by",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/jst/jst-gen/50.24"},["span.small","JST"],"Gen. 50:24 (Appendix)"],"and was fulfilled in Jesus Christ’s being literally of the lineage so as to be the heir to the throne of David.",["i","Shiloh"],"can be read as a short form for “He to whom it belongs”; for such a phrase referring to the Messiah, see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezek/21.27"},"Ezek. 21:27"],"."]]],"refs":null}
